body:
Designing in several phases.

__Design Phase One : Core functionality__
- Main activity with 2 options : enroll and verify
- Respective activities with image capturing
- In the backend, they encode the image and call the Kairos API, print success/failure
- No class segregation, no user accounts, no DB

- Subsequent phases will have the unimplemented features mentioned in the last line above
- Order of implementation for now seems to be:
    - DB : no point of app w/o this. there needs to be record keeping. Simple attendance for each day.
    - Class segregation : Attendance as per different classes. Simulates real world
    - User accounts : Least important from project point of view. Will involve user registering on Kairos and entering app ID/key during registration. Unless we use the same ID/key. this step should make it real world ready with security and what not.
title: Design - Face recognition

In either case, the email verification step can be in magic link setup, linked to a button to verify email. If we accept email as username, we'll send to that address; if we accept usernames of any kind, we'll have a field asking for email, and send to that.

body:
- [x] Create design/prototype for text mining. (Zubin. ETA : Feb 13. Extended to Feb 18)
Following summarizes the design for text mining approach 
1. Get reviews/contents from Piazza
2. For each course, convert them into Vector (Using Doc2Vec data algorithm) 
3. From the Doc2Vec model, get the similar words to a list of words we are interested in. (For example : Professor, Rating, Course, Difficulty etc) 
4. Compare the output from Doc2Vec model to a set of Good Words and Bad Words (These set of good and bad words are available on the internet) 
5. Compute a rating for each course - count(good)/(count(good) + count(bad))

body:
A low bandwidth news app where a user can choose his preferences of news. We have a designed three solutions for the same,

1. Web Application: We are planning to create a web application in Python flask that allows the user to create an account and view latest news according to his preferences.

2. A news reader: A text-to-speech generator that can read the news to the user.

3. A text-based news delivery system: News delivered in the form of text message, particularly targeted in users with limited Internet  accessibility.

References:
1. Personalized news recommendation based on click behavior :  http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=1719976
2. A contextual-bandit approach to personalized news article recommendation : http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=1772758
3. Multilingual Information Retrieval and Smart News Feed Based on Big Data : http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/7396613/?reload=true&arnumber=7396613&tag=1
4. Personalized news retrieval system : https://www.google.com/patents/US20050028194 
5. An adaptive personalized news dissemination system : http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10844-008-0053-8
